  "text": "Contributions: We study a variation of the receding-horizon control under the replay attacks. A set of sufficient conditions are provided to ensure asymptotical and exponential stability. More importantly, we derive a simple and explicit relation between the infinite-horizon cost and the computing and attacking horizons. By using such relation, we characterize a class of competitive (resp. cooperative) resource allocation problems for resilient networked control systems as convex games (resp. programs). The preliminary results are published in [CITATION_1] where receding-horizon control is used to deal with a class of deception attacks. The complete version can be found in [CITATION_2] .",
